I've always wanted to see Adeptus Titanicus expand into some sort of weird grimdark version of Battletech. That means lots of new Titans, Knights, and weapons. I did a bunch of [https://cults3d.com/en/3d-model/game/gatling-cannons-compatible-with-the-at18-cerastus-knight](gatling cannons) in the past, but got some requests to do a variant, so here we are!

These Vindex Pattern Gatling Cannons were designed to be compatible with the AT18 scaled Cerastus Knight.

This kit includes the following items:
1) Five different left arm Vindex Pattern Gatling Cannons
2) Five different right arm Vindex Pattern Gatling Cannons

Please do not share or sell these files (including prints and remixes) without my written permission.

An alternative shield and arm for a Cerastus Knight Lancer, made for the AT2018 Cerastus Knight.

Along with the new shield, the arm comes in 3 pieces; upper arm, forearm connector and hand. This allows the forearm to be angled as required and the hand rotated to any angle, facilitating it to be used as a left or right hand, as desired.
Shield on its own is also compatible with the original Cerastus Knight Lancer arms.

Files included: STL, pre-supported STL and full Lychee scene of all parts (in the ZIP file) - should you want/need to tweak the supports for your particular printer.

This piece is made to complement my (Free) Cerastus Knight Trident Lance, available here:
https://cults3d.com/:941267


Note:
This is for the 8mm, AT2018, Cerastus knights
As with the Cerastus Trident Lance, the upper arm comes with a moulded pin so that it can be swapped in and out (once the corresponding hole has been drilled in the original shoulder piece). Just cut this off after printing if you do not intend to swap weapons on your Cerastus Knight.

Justification du tag SUP :

Files included: STL, pre-supported STL and full Lychee scene of all parts (in the ZIP file) - should you want/need to tweak the supports for your particular printer.

Printable Heavy Beamers to arm your Porphy with to make use of it as a counts as Aster. Included are suitable files for both 8mm and 28mm Scale Grimdark kits.

Any parts with the mirror tag mean you need to mirror a copy for the opposite arm fitout. To make a complete pair of arms you will need to print out the mirrored parts plus a second copy of the unmirrored parts.

Note because of the tight fit I couldn't quite get the body side cabling to fit without hitting other parts of the model so I recommend leaving them off.

Printed out fine on my Photon at 0.03mm and on my Saturn at 0.05mm in Monocure Rapid Gunmetal.

30/06/2021: Added the 28mm scale armour mount that had been missed in the mass upload.

06/06/2021:
Added the Following:
Two types of Hull Volkites for converting the Porphy into an Aster Proxy.
Type A - Replaces the hull weapon mount entirely.
Type B - Easy to use magnets in the ball socket allowing you to freely swap between the lascannon and autocannon

07/07/2021
Added Supported Versions of the 8mm Scale Parts suitable for printing on Photon/Mars Sized Printers (Superfine Supports). Includes Hull Beamer Type A, Armour and Main Beamer Body.

21/01/2024
Added the unsupported Shoulder Platelate for 8mm as a customer let me know I had forgotten to include it.

Justification du tag SUP :

Added Supported Versions of the 8mm Scale Parts suitable for printing on Photon/Mars Sized Printers (Superfine Supports). Includes Hull Beamer Type A, Armour and Main Beamer Body. Added the unsupported Shoulder Platelate for 8mm as a customer let me know I had forgotten to include it.

Remix of various Knight parts with some custom CAD parts to flesh it out, bare hulls to allow for Armour swaps. Pre-Scaled to print at 1:1.

I added struts to some of the overhangs that were difficult to add supports to so you can string them off those (particularly the on the legs)

Note when adding the rear hip cables glue the middle first then when that is set use a hairdryer to heat up the resin and bend the ends into place (use a toothpick or the tip of your scalpel to add the superglue).

The carapace is fairly tight of a fit around the exhausts. I used a needle file to bevel the lower part of the hole and glued it on before painting.

Also included the following:
- Remix of "Quest bot Magaera upgrade AT" by TrueGrits617 - I split up the files into individual parts plus reversed the layout of the carapace and added some grab handles to make it more accurate to the 40k version
- Included some files with supports already added mine printed fine on the Photon with these where they are.

Added 14/08/19 -
- Hekaton Claw Arm with both the Styrix and Mahaera Claw Tips.


Added 15/08/219 -
Styrix Pattern Head, well a fair approximation, in High Poly model.


Serious Note: This was a personal project, to test to see how far I could push the detail on my Photon. it would have been far easier for me to just buy the plastic kits and remix just the armour and weapons lol
